<TITLE> New MPO schools list starts off Sept </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 22 (bdnews24.com)  The government will resume listing non-government and private education institutions under the Monthly Pay Order scheme by the first week in September after finalising its new MPO policy, the prime minister's adviser on education Alauddin Ahmed said Wednesday. Alauddin was speaking at the second meeting of a ten-member committee, formed in June, to formulate comprehensive new guidelines for MPO allocation and enlistment of new educational institutions. The committee headed by Alauddin will finalise its policy within seven meetings, he said. The next meeting is due on July 26. Wednesday's meeting discussed various issues in the current policydiverse inconsistencies and ambiguities regarding MPO allocation. He pointed out that corruption took place due to these ambiguities and inconsistencies. "We will formulate a transparent, clear and up-to-date policy with a sympathetic and generous view. No individuals or institutions will be politically deprived here." The government began its work to bring non-government private educational institutions under MPO scheme again after a hiatus of four years during which no new schools were listed. The government allocated Tk. 112 crore in the current 2009-10 budget for new allocations. b
